      'Keeping your diesel generator clean isn’t just about appearance — it’s essential for performance, efficiency, and long-term reliability. Dust, oil residue, and carbon buildup can quietly reduce your generator’s output and even lead to costly repairs if ignored. Regular cleaning helps your generator run smoother, last longer, and stay ready when you need it most — especially during unexpected power outages.',
      'If you’re a homeowner who relies on a generator, the good news is that basic cleaning doesn’t require advanced skills. With the right approach, you can handle it yourself safely and effectively.',
      '## Why Cleaning Matters',
      'Over time, dirt and debris can accumulate in and around your generator. This buildup restricts airflow, affects fuel combustion, and can cause overheating. A clean generator operates more efficiently, consumes fuel properly, and reduces the risk of sudden breakdowns. Regular cleaning also gives you a chance to inspect parts early and catch small issues before they turn into major problems.',
      '## Safety First',
      'Before you begin any cleaning, always make sure the generator is turned off and completely cooled down. Working on a hot generator can be dangerous and may cause burns or damage sensitive components. Disconnect the power supply and allow enough time for all parts to cool. Safety should always come first.',
