      'Start with the generator’s outer body. Dust, grease, and grime tend to settle on the surface, especially if the generator is placed outdoors or in a garage. Use a dry cloth or a soft brush to remove loose dirt. For stubborn stains, a slightly damp cloth with mild detergent works well. Avoid using excessive water, as it can seep into internal components.',
